LORE khephari
FLAGS KHEPHARI
Scarab-beetle folk; large, chitinous humanoids; overlapping chitinous plates
from polished obsidian through iridescent blue-green to desert-sand brown;
curved horn-protrusions swept back from the brow
Hands replaced by broad chitinous claws; can hold weapons and tools but not
gloves or finger rings; compound eyes perceive polarized light for desert
sun-navigation even in featureless terrain
Speak with resonant thorax-buzz that carries well in open desert
Theology: the larva-to-adult molting is called the "first death"; elders
who survive a second great transformation become "Twice-Turned"
Built the roads to and from the Great Pyramid during the Solar Court Era,
not the Pyramid itself; they remember that distinction with quiet pride
Desert route knowledge: their beetle-pilgrimage paths predate Keeper survey
roads; their sand-road engineering is the most reliable available in the
eastern desert
~
